.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course has three general aims: * to develop understanding of the process of learning and establishing essential conditions for learning; * to develop skills for designing learning and instruction, and  also upbringing; * to develop understanding of the essence and aims of assessment.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the student will: * be aware of and values the main theories of learning and motivation in the process of designing instruction and upbringing; * design the process of instruction and upbringing based on evidence and values by choosing purposeful and relevant study and assessment methods, while considering students' individuality, needs, interests as well as underlying national documents; * reflect on learning and instruction design as well as assessment process based on introduced theories.
